More Obituaries for Gary West


Looking for an obituary for a different person with this name?












Gary L. West


Obituary
Condolences




























						WEST Gary L. West, 65, of Columbus, passed away Saturday, November 24, 2012. He was a US Army veteran and graduate of Ohio University. Gary was a member of the Ohio University Alumni Association; retired from the Social Security Administration; and was scorekeeper for Reynoldsburg Girls Basketball for many years. He was preceded in death by his parents Norman and Kathryn West and brother Norman Kenneth West, Jr. Gary is survived by his sons, Anthony and Eric West; nephews, Karey and Kris West; niece, Kori West McCollum; former wife and forever friend, Vicky Mitchell; many dear friends and members of the Reynoldsburg Athletic Association. Family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Wednesday at COTNER FUNERAL HOME, 7369 E. Main St., Reynoldsburg, where the funeral will be held at 10 a.m. Thursday. Burial will follow at Glen Rest Memorial Estate. In lieu of flowers, contributions may be made to the Reynoldsburg Athletic Department. Messages may be sent to his family by visiting www.cotnerfuneralhome.com.



Published in The Columbus Dispatch on Nov. 27, 2012


